    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "For this it might make more sense to hook this into your search client itself. In rough terms this would be:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst algoliaSearchClient = algolisearch('...', '...');\r\n\r\nconst searchClient = {\r\n  search: function(requests) {\r\n    return algoliaSearchClient.search(requests).then(result => {\r\n      // do your api call here\r\n    })\r\n  },\r\n  searchForFacetValues: function(requests) {\r\n    return algoliaSearchClient.searchForFacetValues(requests)\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou then pass `searchClient` as an argument to `instantsearch({ searchClient })`",
